### PRA*S*NA I, ADHYÂYA 8, KA*ND*IKÂ 16.

1\. There are four castes (var*n*a, viz.) Brâhma*n*as, Kshatriyas,
Vai*s*yas, and *S*ûdras. <span id="fr_975"></span>[1](#fn_975.md)

2\. (Males) belonging to them (may take) wives according to the order of
the castes, (viz.) a Brâhma*n*a four, <span
id="fr_976"></span>[2](#fn_976.md)

3\. A Kshatriya three,

4\. A Vai*s*ya two,

5\. A *S*ûdra one.

6\. Sons begotten on (wives) of equal or of the next lower castes (are
called) Savar*n*as (of equal caste). <span
id="fr_977"></span>[6](#fn_977.md)

7\. (Those born) of (wives) of the second or third lower castes (become)
Ambash*th*as, Ugras, and Nishâdas. <span id="fr_978"></span>[7](#fn_978.md)

8\. Of females wedded in the inverse order of the castes (are born)
Âyogavas, Mâgadhas, Vai*n*as, Kshatt*ri*s, Pulkasas, Kukku*t*akas,
Vaidehakas, and *K*a*nd*âlas. <span id="fr_979"></span>[8](#fn_979.md)

9\. An Ambash*th*a (begets) on a female of the first (caste) a
*S*vapâka,

10\. An Ugra on a female of the second (caste) a Vai*n*a,

11\. A Nishâda on a female of the third (caste) a Pulkasa.

<span id="page_197">p. 197</span>

12\. In the contrary case a Kukku*t*aka (is produced).

